---
title: Data Flow — Logging a Set and Getting a Recommendation
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Client as Browser (app.js)
    participant Server as Flask Server (app.py)
    participant Rec as recommendation.py
    participant DB as db.py
    participant SQLite as workout.db

    Note over User,SQLite: ── Logging a completed set ──

    User->>Client: Fills in weight & reps, clicks "Log Set"
    Client->>Server: POST /api/exercises/3/sets\n{ "date": "2026-06-05", "weight": 100, "reps": 7 }
    Server->>DB: insert_set(exercise_id=3, date, weight, reps)
    DB->>SQLite: INSERT INTO sets ...
    SQLite-->>DB: new row id = 42
    DB-->>Server: { "id": 42 }
    Server-->>Client: 201 Created\n{ "id": 42, "exercise_id": 3, "weight": 100, "reps": 7 }
    Client->>User: Shows "Set logged!" confirmation

    Note over User,SQLite: ── Fetching the next-session recommendation ──

    User->>Client: Views "Next Session" panel
    Client->>Server: GET /api/exercises/3/recommendation
    Server->>DB: get_history(exercise_id=3)
    DB->>SQLite: SELECT date, weight, reps FROM sets\nWHERE exercise_id=3 ORDER BY date
    SQLite-->>DB: rows [ {date, weight, reps}, ... ]
    DB-->>Server: list of dicts
    Server->>Rec: recommend(history, rep_range_low=5,\nrep_range_high=8, weight_increment=5.0)
    Rec-->>Server: { "weight": 100, "reps": 8, "note": "..." }
    Server-->>Client: 200 OK\n{ "weight": 100, "target_reps": 8, "note": "..." }
    Client->>User: Shows "Next session: 100 lb × 8 reps"
